# Git Workflow

## Branch Protection (MANDATORY)

- **NEVER push directly to `master`** — not regular push, not force push, not with `--no-verify`.
- **NEVER force push** to any branch. If asked by the user, warn them and only proceed if they explicitly confirm.
- Always create a feature/fix branch (e.g. `fix/description`, `feat/description`) for every change.
- Commit on the branch, push the branch, then open a PR targeting `master`.
- The user will review and merge PRs themselves after CI is green.

## Workflow

1. `git checkout -b <type>/<short-description>` from `master`
2. Make changes, commit with conventional commit messages
3. `git push -u origin <branch-name>`
4. `gh pr create --base master --title "..." --body-file <tmp-file>`
5. Clean up any temp files used for PR body
6. Report the PR URL to the user
